{"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/MdocDataModel18013\/documentation\/MdocDataModel18013\/CredentialPolicy\/rotateUse"},"sections":[],"kind":"symbol","primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"case"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"rotateUse"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When a credential is used, its usage count is incremented, allowing the system"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to distribute load across multiple available credentials. This approach balances"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"security with performance considerations by enabling credential reuse while"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"maintaining usage patterns for auditing and optimization purposes."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Appropriate for scenarios requiring frequent authentication where the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"performance overhead of continuous credential generation would be prohibitive."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"metadata":{"symbolKind":"case","role":"symbol","roleHeading":"Case","externalID":"s:18MdocDataModel1801316CredentialPolicyO9rotateUseyA2CmF","modules":[{"name":"MdocDataModel18013"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"case"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"rotateUse"}],"title":"CredentialPolicy.rotateUse"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/MdocDataModel18013\/documentation\/MdocDataModel18013","doc:\/\/MdocDataModel18013\/documentation\/MdocDataModel18013\/CredentialPolicy"]]},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/mdocdatamodel18013\/credentialpolicy\/rotateuse"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Policy that manages credential rot